# 🏢 SQL Data Warehouse Project
A full-stack SQL-based data warehouse project simulating real-world CRM and ERP systems. It processes structured data through a Bronze → Silver → Gold pipeline using T-SQL, ready for use in Business Intelligence tools like Power BI.

This project demonstrates data ingestion, cleansing, transformation, dimensional modeling, and reporting, following industry best practices in naming, modularity, and schema layering.


---

## 🧠 Use Case

Simulates a retail business integrating sales, product, and customer datasets to enable:

- 📈 Customer insights & segmentation  
- 📦 Product performance analysis  
- 💸 Sales behavior tracking  
- 📊 Dashboards via Power BI or Tableau

---

## 📐 Architecture Overview

The project follows the **Lakehouse-inspired layered architecture:


                     ┌─────────────┐
                     │ Source Data │
                     └─────┬───────┘
                           ▼
                     ┌─────────────┐
                     │  Bronze     │  ← Raw ingestion
                     └─────┬───────┘
                           ▼
                     ┌─────────────┐
                     │  Silver     │  ← Cleaning, joins, standardization
                     └─────┬───────┘
                           ▼
                     ┌─────────────┐
                     │   Gold      │  ← BI-ready views (facts, dims)
                     └─────────────┘


  ## 🔄 Data Flow

### 📥 Bronze Layer
- Raw data from CRM & ERP systems  
- No transformation logic — only schema mapping

### ⚙️ Silver Layer
- Cleaning nulls, whitespaces, and invalid values  
- Joining CRM & ERP datasets  
- Type casting and value normalization  
- Application of business rules  

### 🪙 Gold Layer
Final analytical views for reporting:
- `dim_customers`  
- `dim_products`  
- `fact_sales`  

---

## 🧹 Transformation Breakdown

### 🔧 Cleansing Tasks:
- Remove duplicates  
- Handle nulls, white spaces  
- Detect outliers  
- Filter bad records  

### 🧠 Enrichment & Logic:
- Derive new keys or columns (e.g., `category_id`)  
- Integrate data from multiple systems  
- Normalize values (e.g., country codes)  
- Format values for consistency (e.g., `prd_line` → `Mountain`)  

---

## 🗂️ Dataset Dictionary

| Table Name           | Layer   | Description                             | Key Fields           |
|----------------------|---------|------------------------------------------|-----------------------|
| `crm_cust_info`      | Bronze  | Raw CRM customer master                  | `cst_id`, `cst_key`   |
| `crm_prd_info`       | Bronze  | Product information                      | `prd_id`, `prd_key`   |
| `crm_sales_details`  | Bronze  | CRM transactional data                   | `cst_key`, `prd_key`  |
| `erp_cust_az12`      | Bronze  | ERP customer table                       | `cid`, `gndr`, `cntry`|
| `erp_loc_a101`       | Bronze  | Location master                          | `loc_id`, `cntry`     |
| `erp_px_cat_g1v2`    | Bronze  | Product-category mapping                 | `prd_key`, `cat_id`   |
| `dim_customers`      | Gold    | Final customer dimension                 | `customer_key`        |
| `dim_products`       | Gold    | Final product dimension                  | `product_key`         |
| `fact_sales`         | Gold    | Cleaned transactional fact table        | `sls_key`, `prd_id` |

---

## 🚀 How to Use

### 1️⃣ Clone the Repo
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/Sql_DataWareHouse_Project.git
## 🚀 How to Use

### 2️⃣ Load Raw Tables (Bronze)
Run the SQL scripts located in the `/bronze/` folder to load raw data from CRM and ERP systems into staging tables.

### 3️⃣ Apply Transformations (Silver Layer)
Execute the scripts in the `/silver/` folder to:
- Join ERP and CRM data sources
- Clean and standardize the datasets
- Create intermediate, refined transformation tables

### 4️⃣ Build Final Views (Gold Layer)
Run the SQL views to generate final analytical tables:
- `gold.dim_customers`
- `gold.dim_products`
- `gold.fact_sales`
